def: A table of mortality computed from the experience of one ormore life-insurance companies.

To declaim or rail (against some person or thing); to uttercensorious and bitter language; to attack with harsh criticism orreproach, either spoken or written; to use invectives; -- withagainst; as, to inveigh against character, conduct, manners, customs,morals, a law, an abuse.All men inveighed against him; all men, except court vassals, opposedhim. Milton.The artificial life against which we inveighed. Hawthorne.
An argument retorted on an opponent. Milton.
Antidotal.-- n. Antidote; also, a book of antidotes.
One whose manners or ideas are fantastic. [R.] Coleridge.
A combining form from Gr. stone.
Any butterfly of the tribe Nymphalidi, or genus Basilarchia, asthe ursula and the viceroy.
Of or pertaining to the syrinx; as, the syringeal muscle.
Incapable of doing either harm or good, as some medicines.Dunglison.
